vera++
------------------------------------------
Vera++ is a programmable tool for verification, analysis and transformation of
C++ source code. Vera++ is mainly an engine that parses C++ source files and
presents the result of this parsing to scripts in the form of various
collections - the scripts are actually performing the requested tasks.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.20-1
  libboost1.53-1.53.0-2
  libgcc1-4.7.3-1
  libstdc++6-4.7.3-1
  tcl-8.5.11-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.23.51-1
  cmake-2.8.9-2
  cygport-0.12.2-1
  gcc4-core-4.7.3-2
  gcc4-g++-4.7.3-2
  make-3.82.90-1
  tcl-8.5.11-1

Canonical website:
  https://bitbucket.org/verateam/vera

Canonical download:
  https://bitbucket.org/verateam/vera/downloads/vera++-1.2.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack vera++-1.2.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
         unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./vera++-1.2.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/vera++-1.2.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/vera++-1.2.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

